e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[With a virus as widespread around the country as this one, there are bound
to be cases where a virus-positive pig farm is missed and an infected
animal reaches the slaughterhouse. We are, of course, assuming that this
case has been confirmed by laboratory tests. Now the important thing is to
identify the points of risk in the carcass-marking process. It would also
be interesting to know if the fatal case was immunodeficient, making him
susceptible to a very low infective dose of the virus. - Mod.JW
......................................jw/es
